snippet.textDisplay: 1:23:52

Very controversial fight, very close one, too but I think the judges got it right besides the 49-46 guy. Jones’ defense was impeccable, and I think he definitely won rounds 2, 4 and 5, got some big strikes in and takedowns when it counted the most. Reyes seemed to be coasting through the 5th round, and when you’re the challenger, you can’t let it go to the judges like that. Just like the president, Jones has a sort of incumbent advantage. Could’ve gone either way, though honestly. Both of them deserved it. Great fight.
snippet.textOriginal: Very controversial fight, very close one, too but I think the judges got it right besides the 49-46 guy. Jones’ defense was impeccable, and I think he definitely won rounds 2, 4 and 5, got some big strikes in and takedowns when it counted the most. Reyes seemed to be coasting through the 5th round, and when you’re the challenger, you can’t let it go to the judges like that. Just like the president, Jones has a sort of incumbent advantage. Could’ve gone either way, though honestly. Both of them deserved it. Great fight.

snippet.textDisplay:
I think when people watch a fight in "real-time", and the challenger puts up a good fight, fans clamor that the challenger won. Everyone likes the underdog story, especially if the champ isn't well liked, but let's be objective.
Round 1 - Clearly Reyes
Round 2 - Clearly Jones
Round 3 - Very Close Round, toss up
Round 4 - Slightly Jones
Round 5 - Clearly Jones

Jones won.
Also, after reading the comments, I was expecting the commentary to be egregiously biased, so I watched the fight without sound, then with sound. I can honestly say that they called the fight beautifully. Completely objective commentary. The bias is from y'all, the fans.
snippet.textOriginal:
I think when people watch a fight in "real-time", and the challenger puts up a good fight, fans clamor that the challenger won. Everyone likes the underdog story, especially if the champ isn't well liked, but let's be objective. 
Round 1 - Clearly Reyes
Round 2 - Clearly Jones
Round 3 - Very Close Round, toss up
Round 4 - Slightly Jones
Round 5 - Clearly Jones

Jones won.
Also, after reading the comments, I was expecting the commentary to be egregiously biased, so I watched the fight without sound, then with sound. I can honestly say that they called the fight beautifully. Completely objective commentary. The bias is from y'all, the fans.
